When paying a certain price, it is always nice to feel like you are getting something a bit "extra", however small it might be.	I read the wonderful reviews on TripAdvisor and was able to get a room in the main house for a very reasonable price.	They get a lot of money for the rooms and it would cost very little to do this.	The Marquesa was the perfect choice; and aside from a great location, this hotel has character, and a fantastic staff, all for reasonable prices.	We stayed many times before at this high-reputation hotel, but returning this Feb with friends we found that the mid-range price was now extended to the cheaper rooms.